    "body": "Problem:\r\nPR #29833 has found its way to stable Neovim release, which is a source of [confusion to beginners](https://matrix.to/#/!cylwlNXSwagQmZSkzs:matrix.org/$Ofj-TFIsEMbp0O9OhE8xuZSNi-nhRLtZTOgs6JRLNrs?via=matrix.org&via=gitter.im&via=mozilla.org), because lesson 2.6 requires users to undo the text, which makes the \"wrong\" mark comes back. This is a limitation with the old implementation which always depends on absolute line numbers\r\n\r\nSolution:\r\nPort #34921, #34989, #34996, which switch implementation to extmarks, to fix it. Also port #34803 because #34921 depends (a bit) on #34803\r\n\r\nI have tried all built-in tutors with new implementations, and they should work\r\n\r\nFix #28164, #32325, #16122\r\n",
